business_name: Kin Coworking Space NYC : Affordable shared office Space NYC & Soho
formatted_address: 442 Broadway 2nd floor, New York, NY 10013, USA
text: So I recently started my modeling career. Applying for ton of adds and etc. Some of it legit, some not. Today one "lady" contacted me and invited for a casting right that day. "oh, well maybe they are in the rush, whatever" - I thought. I didn't have the right clothing for casting, so I let her know, she said it's fine. "kkk" it got fishy when she said I gotta call her, when I reach the address. why is that??? They don't have an office or secretary?! Alright, I still went, to see what's it about. I got there, she never introduced herself nor gave me a name of the agency. I walked in the nice office, but there was no front desk or anything like that. She brought me to one of the rooms, showed me some kinda website of the agency, that didn't contein of anything but photos of girls. And she got forward to the deal/scam. We will put your photos on our website and connect with clients for $100 one time fee, we don't charge % of work you do with clients it's all yours!! Oh, WOW, such a great deal and only $100!!! Sign me in rn!! Like really??? You would consistently connect me with clients without getting paid, applauds!! Whatta angel! Nope! No legitimate agent will ask you money upfront and denies taking a fee if you booked, otherwise it doesn't worth it to them nor they interested in getting work done. She kept rushing with an answer, if I gonna pay, plus they were shooting rn for future catalog. Duh, probably for more buzz and excitement for "Green" model. After I said :"no, thank you!" she looked dissatisfied and showed me the door, there was another girl waiting. After I left I Googled kin spaces, they are legit, BUT it's coworking space and anybody can rent a space there to work even scamers, unfortunately. Be careful ladies!! Your, Velvet cat on the sun

text: I have been in several co-working spaces over the past 2 years and The Commons has shown a nice, familiar atmosphere. Co-working is all about  working in a space where you meet your neighbors and this actually happens at The Commons, which has been a rarity in other co-working locations. The built-in office furniture is beautiful and professional looking and the staff is very helpful. I got locked out of my office one evening and the owner got back to me very quickly, helped me resolve the situation and saved the day! I wouldn't have been able to get into my office that night if I didn't have direct access and familiarity with the founder. If you're looking for a professional setting and an actual connection with your neighbors and staff, The Commons is a great place to work!

formatted_address: 157 East 86th St 5th Floor, New York, NY 10128, USA

- Clean toilets. Never had a problem. 

- FLAWLESS WiFi. Nuff said. 

- Open 24 hours a day with flawless electronic locks on the building door and office door.

text:
Best co-working space in NYC hands down. While others can compete on the office design and amenities, no one can compete with the staff here. At Alley they have built a strong community, so you don’t just rent a desk or office, you join a family that’s always there to help you. The networking and support between members of Alley is far above average in my opinion. 

Honestly speaking, the other spaces has nothing on Alley. To top it off Alley is Now powered by Verizon. So if your in tech, joining the Chelsea location will give you access to next gen 5G. No one else can offer that.

text: Great facilities, great staff, the atmosphere was charged with innovation and productivity. Uplifting place to go and be somewhere and do something!

formatted_address: 135 Madison Ave floor 8, New York, NY 10016, USA
text: Blender Workspace is an aesthetically pleasing, charming and attractive space. My company recently held our Holiday Party at the bar lounge space at Blender. Everyone raved about how great the space was and asked how I found this gem of a venue in New York City. I can take credit for finding this venue but all of it wouldn’t have been possible without Jessica and her team at Blender. They helped with absolutely anything that was needed and was very patient through all the party planning and budgeting. If you are looking for a venue for a company party, happy hour for a client, an event with a speaker, or just want to get some work done and grab a coffee during the day… Blender Workspace is the rare find you’ve been looking for. I highly recommend this space and I recommend even higher the events director, Jessica.

formatted_address: 135 Madison Ave floor 8, New York, NY 10016, USA
text: The Blender Workspace is an incredible communal space with amazing art, an amazing atmosphere, and really delicious coffee! They are also a fantastic venue for corporate events! We've had a number of happy hours in the gallery and they are always a hit.

formatted_address: 135 Madison Ave floor 8, New York, NY 10016, USA
text:

formatted_address: 135 Madison Ave floor 8, New York, NY 10016, USA
text: I couldn't be more thrilled my experience with Blender space. I hosted the art and music event Trip N Draw and the Blender team was there to assist me from start to finish - from creating beautiful animations and graphics for promotional materials, to setting up all our AV gear, to arranging the furniture to suit our format. The Blender team was quick to respond to our needs and went above and beyond to ensure our guests had a wonderful experience. The space itself exudes luxury, with its bright natural light with large windows, chic furniture and decor, and expansive white walls. I will definitely be back for more events at Blender.

formatted_address: 219 36th St, Brooklyn, NY 11232, USA
text:
UPDATED: They are now open on Saturday. Great News!!

A true hidden gem in Brooklyn. Spacious work space area with plenty of work tables and resources. As a freelance artist, I have plenty of surface area to spread out my digital work station and work without feeling cramped or pressured to move. Staff are all friendly and easy to talk to. Quick and easy for me to get the area from the R Train in Brooklyn. I haven't yet had the chance to explore the local eateries, but they all look great. I rented a locker to store my stuff in the basement workspace area so that I don't need to carry items to and fro from my apartment. I signed up for one year membership at a very affordable fee. My only wish was there was a kitchen where I could microwave my lunch and that the common work share area was open during the weekend.

They also have many different creams and literally anything you might need to get ready to go out after work. In the shower room they have towels and slippers and they even have deodorant. This place is perfect to get ready for work after you go to the gym or to freshen up before you go out after work. Everything is always very clean. They recently added another floor and there is plenty of place to work. You can either work at a table or while sitting on the couch. They have something for everyone!

text:
SoTechie is in the lower half of the coworking spaces I have been to in New York. The really low quality website is probably a good indicator of that. The only big plus over places in the area is the internet speed, which I clocked at 37M down and 17M up using speedtest.

The space doesn't have the quality that most other spaces in the area have. I found that there was a weird smell that took a while to get used to. The bathrooms were not well maintained and the kitchen area had dirty dishes in the sink. Having been to 5 other coworking spaces within a few weeks in New York, I think it is safe to say that SoTechie is one of the worse ones.

That's not to say it is really bad though, just not great. Considering its proximity to other places like WeWork, Ensemble and The Productive, it is a tough sell.

formatted_address: 114 E 25th St, New York, NY 10010, USA
text:
I am sure this was just my experience, as I know several (very awake and open) members and really align with the core idea, but after several days in New York, the only time I felt unwelcome was when I attempted to attend an event here after travelling a significant distance, only to be turned away due to rigorous formality.

Great people and a powerful vision, but unfortunately, it seems there may be a bit of posturing that prevents it from truly achieving it's potential, at least for me.

Maybe if I I am in town again, I can give it another chance.

Just to clarify, the staff member who worked with me was very nice. They were not directly rude and suggested a cheaper, more accessible event after refusing me entry (which was a bit weird in the assumption, not going to lie, but it was kind). Please, please do not take this as a reflection of their character. Just a bit of a slip in judgement perhaps imho.

formatted_address: 215 Park Ave S floor 11, New York, NY 10003, USA
text: Having previously worked in communal office spaces, Industrious, by comparison, is an exceptional, high end experience amongst some pretty mediocre work spaces. For companies who require a higher-end brand experience, supportive staff, GREAT coffee and bagels, events and amenities, without a luxury price tag, look no further. I love it here. Krissy & Sarah get it done.

formatted_address: 215 Park Ave S floor 11, New York, NY 10003, USA
text: Industrious is beautiful, professional and the staff is super helpful and friendly.  Great place to work and bring clients back to with the homey, yet professional common areas and great conference rooms to hold meetings in.  Breakfast, coffee and snacks daily, plus a weekly HH are great perks as well!  Even better, you don't hear ping pong balls smashing around all day like you would at other, less serious co-working spaces!

formatted_address: 215 Park Ave S floor 11, New York, NY 10003, USA
text: I was a bit skeptical about moving our 11 person NYC office into a co-working space because I'd heard so many horror stories--ticket systems where the staffs' only concern is closing the ticket rather than solving your problem, unprofessional environment where you cannot bring clients, loud neighbors etc. Industrious is anything but that. The staff at Industrious are receptive-taking your ideas and concerns seriously and acting on them immediately. The offices are decently soundproofed and there are many other nooks and crannies to go to if you need to have a private conversation. The environment is extremely professional and we bring clients by the office regularly. As a working parent, I'm extremely impressed with the wellness/pumping room for new mothers and the access to other Industrious spaces which allows me to work closer to home a couple of days per week.  Overall, this is a 5 star space and I'm so happy that we made this decision.

formatted_address: 215 Park Ave S floor 11, New York, NY 10003, USA

formatted_address: 7080 Hollywood Blvd, PH, Los Angeles, CA 90028, USA
text:
I considered several co-working options in the area before choosing Ignited Spaces.  As prices are typically comparable, other criteria drove the decision.

Your priorities may vary, but it's likely that you're considering staff, physical plant, and 'vibe'.  IS was the obvious choice for us.  We've been Ignited Spaces customers since 2016 and the only changes have been improvements.

IS is really well thought out, and very attractively designed.  The common spaces are well-equipped with a playful feel.  The technical infrastructure is solid.

The co-worker spaces are calm and quiet.  The offices are spacious, offering both privacy and light.  Depending on where you land, the views run from good to spectacular.

The staff is perhaps the greatest feature of the facility.  They are welcoming, gracious, and accommodating.  I am consistently amazed, notwithstanding the limited time that I personally spend at IS, that people know me on sight, remembering my name and company affiliation.  In my experience, technical issues were solved in minutes.

The IS location is terrific, with a first-tier independent cafe on the ground floor and good quality, affordable restaurants within walking distance.  If you are considering co-working space, you need look no further.

Overall very happy with our office situation which is a big feat in Los Angeles! Thank you Ignited Spaces Hollywood team for making coming to work a pleasure! xx

text:
Most of my work is done on the move. Using a coworking space became a must after some years developing my own business while keeping costs low. 

I learned about Indie Desk through a friend who recommended it to me. I went to learn more and they gave me a FREE day pass. Next day I managed to do more than I use to achieve when I work in a coffee shop. 

They have good facilities, friendly staff and a cool community of freelancers and entrepreneurs. Something unexpected interacting with the community was that I ended up receiving a free advice from an expert: one of the members who is a video producer with more than 10 years of experience gave me advice to complete a video for marketing a new mobile app.

What I love the most about Indie Desk is its community and the location in Downtown LA. Whether I use my bike or take a bus/metro, I don´t worry about traffic anymore or wasting my time commuting. 

I highly recommend this coworking space to anyone looking for a cool coworking space in a good location with a friendly community.

formatted_address: 1763 N Gower St, Los Angeles, CA 90028, USA
text: The Epiphany Space writing group remains the most consistent that I've found in L.A.!  Weekly meetings with other writers in the heart of Hollywood has given me incredible stability and accountability in my work. Prioritizing my craft amidst the challenges and distractions of maintaining an artistic career in L.A. has been extremely difficult, but because of the community I found at Epiphany Space, I was able to brainstorm and collaborate with artists from a range of media backgrounds. Since I joined Epiphany’s writing group in 2015, I’ve produced a blog, several screenplays, my debut theatrical play, a full-length book, and a publishing proposal. My interactions there even led to other creative opportunities in acting and pitching! The support, direction, and work ethic I've received from Epiphany Space cannot be overstated.

They also hold regular events like Monday Moonlight Music, an open mike night  that runs from Spring to Fall, as well as mixers to create a spirit of community. text:
I come to the Hatchery Press on Wednesdays for the writing workshops they have to offer, which are always very friendly, welcoming, supportive, and incredibly conducive in creating wonderful and surprising works of writing.  The workshops are $5 each, which is awesome, unless you're a member, in which case I believe it's free.

The space is very modern, clean, warm and helps you eliminate distractions that you may otherwise face writing in a coffee shop or at home.  Also, the space offers a bunch of different resources, WiFi and other awesome amenities that every writer needs.

And Talia, the founder of the Hatchery Press, is without a doubt just one of the most awesome people you'll meet in the writing community.  She's very knowledgeable, helpful and welcoming, and very professional in ensuring that every writer has a safe space to write and create at the Hatchery Press.

I've been coming here for a few months now, and it's been great to meet other writers and hear the many wonderful pieces of writing they've created, and to share the writing that I myself have created.  If you haven't checked this place out yet, I would highly recommend it.

text:

formatted_address: 4942 Vineland Ave #2, North Hollywood, CA 91601, USA
text: The North Hollywood facility is open 24 hours, so no getting kicked out just when you're making progress. Sparkling clean kitchen facilities, free wi-fi, printing capabilities. formatted_address: 4942 Vineland Ave #2, North Hollywood, CA 91601, USA
text: After checking out coworking spaces like WeWork and Regus throughout Los Angeles and The Valley, I settled on The Muse Rooms in North Hollywood and I love it! text: This is an interesting building. From the outside, it looks like a normal office building, but the inside is a different story. First, there's no lobby to the building. formatted_address: 113 N San Vicente Blvd, Beverly Hills, CA 90211, USA
text:
I LOST a lot of Money with Dots Spaces  - I had paid for a professional telephone answering services for the whole year in advance. A number was provided by Dots Spaces and this number was then placed on our website, business cards and promo cards. 

The company initially kept my card on file despite that I had paid the whole year in advance and kept charging me every month and every month I had to write to them inquiring that why they were charging me, then go through the refund process until one day I had had enough, I shouldn't have had to deal with this sort of thing. By this time it was already halfway through the year so they removed my card but failed to pay for the line that they had already charged me for, thus the line got disconnected. I was then promised by Yoann (Owner) that the phone number will be recovered as I had already printed it on very expensive promo cards and business cards which was impossible for me to repeat! It is evident from the photos that by July they still have no clue that this account is all paid for!

Moving on I felt reassured by Yoann as he called stating that he had got that exact number back and promised that he would take care of that account personally from then on so that this doesn't happen again. I then went on to promote and market the business, however by December I started to think that something was wrong and that why I didn't even have one inquiry despite all the marketing so I called the number and it was disconnected again, I think I was having a heart attack at the time from the shock. I called in again and this time discovered that they had not managed to get the original number that they had given me so they got a different number and didn't even bother to tell me!!!!

I wrote to Yoann many times requesting of him to take responsibility for the damages he has caused me and truly only asked for a small portion of what I had lost, enough so that I could recover from all the losses but I never got any response of any kind, not even a simple apology!

I had very high regards for Yoann but I'm now highly disappointed. This behavior is highly unprofessional and I would not recommend this company to anyone.

text: Ok let's be real, it's an office, and it's a really nice office. But what I can guarantee is that it has a better office staff than anywhere else in this town. (If you really want a criticism, it is, at the end of the day, a shared workspace...thus you share a kitchen area...and a microwave...meaning you share it with the lady who microwaves fish).  But in all seriousness, it's a great space to work and even feels like a home away from home when you want to smash your head on the keyboard after a long day of work.

They also host small events to keep the offices buzzing and to get to know the other companies throughout the building. 

The offices themselves are very large and the furniture provided is quality. The walls are thick so you never have to worry about having hearing a neighbor on the phone or anything. The views are amazing- you can see all the way to Big Bear on a clear day and Santa Monica in the other direction.

The space feels mature which is one thing we like about it most. There are no "hot desks" that you might find at a WeWork so the shared spaces are never overrun by random people popping in and out. 

We moved from a WeWork and we could not have made a better decision. Absolutely love this place and the staff here!

formatted_address: 641 N Larchmont Blvd, Los Angeles, CA 90004, USA
text:
A gem. I started coming while it was still under construction in February, and have since upgraded to a dedicated desk. I was hopping coffee shops before, and when I did the math I'm not only infinitely more productive now, I'm also saving money! 

You can pick an environment to suit your work mood: well lit open lounge seating, bar high top, large shared tables, dedicated desks, enclosed "phone booths" that are really mini-lounges, head down quiet areas, what have you. Staff is extremely responsive, friendly, and helpful (shout out Catherine and Lani!). There's parking underneath, a bus stop on the corner, and restaurants galore in the area. Coffee is good and plentiful (cold brew on tap is the devil, stick to the fresh ground unless you're a caffeine fiend).

Make sure you actually take the tour, because it took me a month to realize there was additional open seating and window facing phone booths down a hallway I had assumed was all private offices. 

My advice is to get in now, while they're still in the soft opening period and offering great deals to fill the place—because it's only a matter of time until it's full.

I think it strikes the right balance between being a serious place to work without being stuffy.

text:
Ever want to be on a fire truck? You know, behind the wheel? Ever see an octopus with a portable radio? Ever want to start a business? That's what the "Tool Box" is all about. With all the demands on the entrepreneur, starting a new business, sometimes it's better just to be a little playful. To meet with others trying to beat the same path. To dream in the space that allows it without criticism.

That's the Tool Box. Southern California's largest innovation lab, a development and meeting space. There is a sandwich shop and as required, snacks. There is lots of space to meet with your collaborators, subcontractors, or clients. And, don't forget the firetruck. And, the graffitied school bus.

Parking is free and is wheelchair accessible. The price of space and access to the facility is moderate. Everything within the facility is wheelchair accessible.

formatted_address: 73 W Monroe St, Chicago, IL 60603, USA
text: I love my office at Novel! I am a career coach and about 2 years ago I sought out a new space for meeting with my clients. I had previously rented a small room in an office building. Being in a co-working space is so much more enjoyable for the community aspect and networking possibilities. I can walk  out of my office to get an espresso from the amazing (free) coffee machine and run into another Novel member to chat with for a bit between my appointments. When looking at office options I also checked out WeWork and did a hard comparison between the two. The Novel staff had more ability to meet my specific needs, and I was able to get exactly what I needed for my budget. I also love the perk of getting to use of Novel co-working spaces in other cities. I recently visited the San Diego office which has a rooftop! I feel like Novel is a particularly great place to grow your career dreams. I highly recommend renting here!

formatted_address: 73 W Monroe St, Chicago, IL 60603, USA
text: I have been in business for over 20 years and recently needed a second space to help accommodate my patients in the loop. I of course had the expectation of a clean and private space, but what I found at the Level office suites was an incredibly professional and accommodating staff that consistently wants to assist me in any way they can with the development of my business. The tenants are diverse and fun to be around as well and after a little more than a year I consider many of them friends.... In fact, I look forward to going down to that location every time that I am scheduled to do so. The management team is as good as anyone could hope for and the buildings general culture is supportive and very affable. I could not be happier and plan to stay for as long as I am in business. Highest marks possible overall.

formatted_address: 73 W Monroe St, Chicago, IL 60603, USA
text: Novel has been a great place for us to establish and grow our business.  Everyone there is helpful in meeting our ever-changing needs.  They have also built a very collaborative environment which filters through all the businesses that have space in their offices.  As we've grown, we have considered moving into our own office space, but the experience at Novel is so positive, we feel this is really a home for us now and in the future.

formatted_address: 73 W Monroe St, Chicago, IL 60603, USA
text: After sampling a few Chicago coworking spaces we came across Level Office. It is perfect for us! We came for the great Loop location, fast internet, reasonable prices and cool vibe. But once we moved in we realized that the key benefit for startup companies like us (or satellite locations of larger companies) is the “community”. Starting a business can make you feel isolated, especially after experiencing life at a larger company as most entrepreneurs have. Level Office has a great community! Level staff creates events (lunch & learns, happy hours, etc.) which make it easy to meet other people in the location. We’ve made connections that lead to new business, new partners, and new friends. You also can utilize the other Level Office locations if you have a meeting in River North or West Loop, or even in many other cities nationwide. The Level Office staff seems to know everyone by name which makes the place seem cozy even though it’s pretty big. They also have a nice community app which makes it easy to stay in the loop with Level staff, connect with other people in the building, book conference rooms and never miss an event. We are big fans of Level Office – highly recommended!

text:
Excited to be the first to review SPACE! I was invited to co-work here with a friend a few weeks ago, and was really impressed with the lighting, furniture, and balance between startups and individuals working here. What's unique about this space is that the teams that have offices here often work out in the open area. By the second day, I had already met and talked to at least three different startup groups, which is so rare and wonderful, considering I've been comparing co-working spaces for quite awhile. 

The Herman Miller desking offers generous surface area for spreading out, many convenient outlets, and there are skylights sprinkled throughout the space for a natural daylit loft ambiance. It is pretty quiet now, but I think Space will hit a critical mass soon, especially with groups like the Experience Institute making regular appearances. Get in now while you can!

text:
Free Range Office is a great co-working space that feels especially comfortable and home-y. The little patio, variety of tables and seating, and friendly staff keep me coming back every week! Plus, it has 2 phone booths available for use so you can take your meetings and calls in private. 

Quite frankly, one of the biggest perks of the space is that the people here are genuinely friendly and collaborative. We actually talk with each other and meet each other. I have yet to have the same experience at other co-working spaces.

formatted_address: 2, 2141 W North Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA
text: We booked the space for a staff retreat day but hosted our own instead of paying for their services. The place, IMHO, is just ok. It's a bunch of Ikea furniture in a good location. And you pay for the location. You also could pay for mediocre food or $50 if you want people to be able to bring in food. It's not bad but it's not great, especially given the cost. Not to mention that we booked the place for 8:30 to 5:30, so I could set up before the staff arrived at 9 and someone at FRO forgot that we were showing up early. There was no setup time. It all worked out ok but in principle, it could have been better.

formatted_address: 2, 2141 W North Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA
text: Awesome venue and frankly staff. Everything was very professional, Free range office was very large. Seeting arrangement and decorating was very lovely.Thank You!!

formatted_address: 2, 2141 W North Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA
text:
I recently held my baby shower at Free Range Office and absolutely LOVED the space. Hosting the shower in my small apartment was not an option and a restaurant just didn't fit into our budget. After an extensive Google search I came across FRO. While it's original intention is to support the needs of workers and entrepreneurs I could see how the owners expanded their scope of services to include advertising the space as a great place to host some what larger gathers. 

After going to FRO for a walk through I knew it was perfect! My 50 guest would be able to enjoy themselves in the spacious, sunny, clean space and there was even the extra bonus of a small outdoor balcony.  

The day of my baby shower everything went PERFECT. I was able to minimally decorate, the FRO staff helped with table and chair set and break down, my guests were all able to easily park on the street and everyone absolutely loved the space. So many people asked me how I found it. 

I would recommend FRO if you are hosting a small gathering, meeting, book club etc. In addition to it being a beautiful space I also have to mention how reasonably priced it was to host my event there. Obviously getting ready for baby can be very expensive.    FRO gave me the opportunity host family and friends in a classy way without breaking the bank. 

Great concept! I'd definitely recommend checking it out!

formatted_address: 2, 2141 W North Ave, Chicago, IL 60647, USA
text:

formatted_address: 1 N State St #1500, Chicago, IL 60602, USA
text:
Let me start by saying, the office spaces and make staff are excellent. The offices are always clean, there is always fresh coffee brewed, and the staff is attentive and responsive.

However the building the Make offices are in is a hot mess. The elevators are frequently broken making it extremely time consuming to get to the make offices (sometimes people have to wait 10+ minutes for an elevator). The building also houses a school which means that there are frequently young kids blocking the entrance. I've witnessed multiple people raising the issue to the building staff however they really aren't willing to work with the school to resolve the issue.

Finally some tenants don't respect the personal space and needs of other tenants. You can frequently find tenants taking sales or personal calls in front of private offices that they don't lease even though there are private call rooms provided. This lack of respect for others needs can make working in the space a bit more stressful than necessary depending on who you get placed next to.

formatted_address: 1 N State St #1500, Chicago, IL 60602, USA
text: There are several shared office spaces in the Chicago area but when you combine an outstanding staff with a very opportune location – you really get the right spot that cannot be beat! I also believe they are really well priced. They throw member events frequently and the overall vibe is of businesses that are less in the startup phase and more into the second step of their growth. It’s also a fantastic spot to collaborate with other organizations and share your expertise. There are two floors and they are pretty different. This is the only space we have been in where the kitchen is massive and the amenities are fantastic! Every other place we have been to – the fridges were so tiny that everyone was battling for space but not here! The place is cleaned daily and we never have to worry about this. If we want to clean our own space – they have everything we need. The WIFI is really strong as well. The location is also fantastic for getting really inexpensive food, 15 min walk from the lake and minutes away from every CTA line. None of us have to walk very far to get to the office from the train. The area is also fantastic for events that are blocks away, such as the farmers market in the summer, parades, and much more! Give these guys a chance!

text: I've been working at coLab South (Main and Chicago) since 2013 and highly recommend it. This office is near the Metra, the el and plenty of coffee shops and restaurants; also, paid and free parking options are plentiful. The owner, Miguel, is constantly upgrading and improving coLab, and the space is welcoming and large. You can choose to work at a desk or a shared long table, and there's plenty of room for you to work comfortably with a laptop, a meal and your files/personal items. There's wifi, a printer, two conference rooms, two kitchens with coffee and two sets of restrooms. Plus, you get to work alongside other freelancers or small business owners, so there's an opportunity for friendly conversation and networking. You can also catch up with other members at one of the regular happy hours that Miguel hosts. Come and try it out for free for a day; I bet you'll love it!

text: Cool IoT space full of up and coming startups. IoT events happen here weekly and can be found on the Connectory website. Awesome and friendly staff. formatted_address: 222 W Merchandise Mart Plaza #570, Chicago, IL 60654, USA
text:
Went here for the tech week closing party event.

The Connectory brings together startups universities and corporate partners.

Covering 19000 square feet in Chicago's historic Merchandise Mart, the Chicago connectory is founded by Bosch in collaboration with 1871, one of the largest startup incubators in the US.

Connectory is a word play on Connecting and Factory, two Central elements of Bosh's Vision .  It is a space where connections happen among devices, people, and ecosystems as the world prepares for the future of Internet of things and digital transformation.

The connectory features access to mentors from Bosch, 1871, and faculty from Chicago area universities. Open working spaces and project collaboration areas. Event space and workshops, as well as being active in charitable organizations.

I anticipate seeing and hearing great things about the Chicago Connectory

text:
A long story short from a deskpass customer for 17 months... 

Here’s what the Deskpass Co-founders decided to do after their app didn’t charge my credit card after I updated it... 

...they automatically canceled my account, wiped out 54 of my credits, and they refused to give them back to me. They offered me a $49 credit for the next month, ha!

A credit is $12.25. That means they took $661.50 from me and provided zero value in exchange.

I only used the credits maybe 10-15 times in 17 months. 

Nicole and Sam, I signed up for your email list back in 2015 and have been a customer since October 2017. It bums me out that you would treat your customers like this. Oh well. Moving on now. Good luck.

Evolve Her has introduced me to a community of exceptional and talented women who have provided support, generously shared knowledge and helped to motivate me every single day to be better and keep going!! The support, kindness and care of Alicia, Tasha and the EH team is incredible.

The events + workshops that i have attended (as part of my membership) have been both practically helpful, thought provoking and super interesting. The events and workshops have been key to helping me stay creative and connected while i navigate life as an entrepreneur and continue to grow my business. 

Highly recommend! x

text: Fast Internet, Great location, right on the rail. Nice size offices. Exceptional customer service from Kris, She was patient in showing me the building and the offices. Once I signed on I asked her if she could have a whiteboard placed on the wall,  before I moved in it was done!

formatted_address: 405 Main St, Houston, TX 77002, USA
text: I would say disappointing is an understatement. My business partner (my brother) and I were the first tenants on the 7th floor of this co working space and it is to our complete disbelieve the way this place has handled communication, and our overall contract guidelines. My brother is having a second child and I have had to travel a lot so we took our computers home with the plan to turn the office into a client meeting space. The office manager took it upon herself to sublease our space while we still had some of our stuff in there and never once communicated this decision with us. And we’re still paying.. we have never stopped paying.. they moved us to another office on the 5th floor.. which is not what we signed up for on our contract. And so now there’s another company using our space, our curtains, our cords, boards... stuff that we own etc.. we have gone through 3 different people who just send us to the other.. and back and forth. No one answers.. no one calls back.. it’s a mess. This is literally my first review ever.. and it’s with the only intention to let everyone who’s looking for a space here to look somewhere else. Somewhere that will guarantee something like this will never happen. Read your contracts, ask questions, and have a lawyer handy. If you do those 3, don’t be surprised if Novel still screws you over to secure their interests.

formatted_address: 405 Main St, Houston, TX 77002, USA

It seems ridiculous to me that I have to be the one to follow up and call, rather than this company following basic and common customer service standards. It's very frustrating to deal with a company that seems to have no interest in resolving matters with their tenants.

formatted_address: 405 Main St, Houston, TX 77002, USA
text: Our law firm started out in private office space (5 individual offices) on a different floor of the Scanlan Building.  Our corporate office told us that we needed to move into a more traditional office setting.  After looking at offices all over downtown, we could not find anything that didn't require an extensive build out or would have involved a shared office space situation.  When we returned from office hunting, our COO grabbed a flyer from the entrance of the building and learned that Novel Co-Working had the perfect space at a reasonable price.  So instead of moving across downtown, we relocated to a different floor.  The space is perfect for our team.  We still have access to the cool co-working space/lounge that Novel Co-Working has, which includes a really fancy beverage machine (makes coffee like a barista) and beer on tap.  I have not had the opportunity to partake of the beer on tap, but it's nice to know that I can invite family and friends to meet me after work, grab a beer and then head out on the town.

text: We believe Houston is the hub of innovation, so when we were seeking a space in Houston for our Gorilla X Facility, we were hungry for an organically creative energy that could evolve our design minds.... so we walked through a muddy pathway, into a blank canvas of a warehouse and stepped through a dusty plastic construction zone.... formatted_address: 1301 Fannin St #2440, Houston, TX 77002, USA
text:
Simple put: The STATION Team has failed to successfully show that they care about their general members.

Initially I started off as a Revolving member but after my membership requirements changed and I needed to leave my items there regularly, I spoke with a Team Member that was happy to help. I was informed that if I upgraded my membership and paid for a desk then I could leave my items around. I was informed about the security cameras that were placed around and one was in the direction of my desk.

Recently my MacBook pro went missing and I verified that it last synced at the office while I was away. After contacting a STATION Team member I found out that their cameras were no longer active since they took them down during remodeling. Turns out the renovations had been complete for several months before the first incident. Unfortunately, the STATION Team chose not to take proactive action and reconnect the cameras and over the upcoming week, other members items came up missing.

The STATION Team would regularly not respond request about info relating to the issues and often required people to find them in person. Many members have had the same issues with the STATION Team relating to the theft incidents.

On top of that, a new accelerator moved in out of nowhere, and several STATION Members had their "permanent" desk re-assigned without fair warning. 

It has been a fair amount of time that the STATION Team was supposed to contact building security and give a response about the footage related to the incident but have failed. 

Many current members have become disappointed as well as previous Team Members.

Please factor this into consideration if you plan on looking at a membership.

text: The Work Well offers a splendid little taste of what it would be like to work in Silicon Valley or even downtown Houston right in the heart of Cypress. There are a variety of offices, conference rooms, and lease options to meet the needs of a variety of entrepreneurs, consultants, artists, and other creative minds. I appreciate the way this co-working environment is setup… There is the option to have private time and close your office door. At the same time, you have the ability to open your door and network in the coffee bar area, sitting areas, and other shared spaces. The possibilities are endless, and I would have to imagine that many of the best perks of working in this already amazing collaborative environment are still yet to come.

text: Best of the shared office/conference room spaces I've seen. Very professional atmosphere, not the "startup" vibe you get at other co-working buildings. I've been here about a month and the staff has been attentive and responsive to any needs I've had. So as far as things they can control, Servcorp knocks it out of the park. Two things they can't control have been the only minor inconveniences so far- the mobile app for booking conference room space is clunky and not so easy to use; and there is a lot of construction going on around the building that makes getting into the building somewhat difficult. This is just a minor annoyance, and again out of Servcorp's control. Everything else has been awesome!

formatted_address: 2800 Post Oak Blvd Suite 4100, Houston, TX 77056, USA
text:
I have to say that I almost never take the time to leave a review.  I would only bother to do so if something occurred that was completely out of the ordinary. Something I wouldn't expect.  I can't remember the last time I stopped from my busy schedule to do so.  And I am now.

When I walked into Servcorp Houston's office in the Williams tower, I was irritated, frustrated, and on a short leash because I had just spent several hours slogging through the hidden details and convoluted terms and conditions at another temporary office space provider.  I left that meeting and went straight to Servcorp.  When I walked in I was curt and on the edge of being rude as I demanded the straight scoop on the offerings at this location.  I was directed to Kaci, and she was fantastic. She put up with my blunt rudeness in an incredibly professional and friendly manner. She never stopped smiling. She gave me an accurate and quick straight to the point answer for every one of my needling questions. I admit that I can be tough on sales people, but she handled my disagreeable manner perfectly. I was overcome by her positive, friendly, and intelligent answers. She knows her business, and she knows how to handle people.

After what must have for her been a grueling 2 hours of my intense scrutiny, she completely convinced me of the value in the Servcorp offerings, and I signed up for a contract.  And she didn't "sell" me. She did this by politely and positively educating me.  I have to say that I am a fan.  Once our company grows into needing a permanent office in Houston... Servcorp beware. We may try to poach Kaci from you.

formatted_address: 2800 Post Oak Blvd Suite 4100, Houston, TX 77056, USA
text: Absolute first-class service and unparalleled response times!  The team at Servcorp bent over backwards every time my company needed anything.  I cannot say enough good things about them.  If you are looking for office space or a virtual address, this is the best place to call!

text: I've been a member here for about a year now, And I must say, this place is awesome. At first, I was a little unsure. I can see why some people might think the staff members are rude. They aren't on purpose, most are just really busy handling tasks for other members or for the organization. Once you spend some time in here, you'll realize just how helpful and knowledgeable the staff is. The tools are good. A lot of the bigger tools are a little bit older, and they have tons of broken tools donated to them that aren't even usable (not their fault), but over time I have seen how well they take care of what they have and trying to always improve. People forget this is a non-profit and not a business.  This isn't a place that has all the money in the world to be a perfect organization. I'm not even sure how they financially got this far, but it shows in the work and effort they have put into this place. I've brought several of my friends here to show off whats possible to get things from their head to in their hands. If you like working with your hands, this place is for you.

formatted_address: 205 Roberts St, Houston, TX 77003, USA
text:
After multiple visits to TXRX, and extremely helpful conversations with the senior staff, I am writing to endorse this organization. Some months ago, I was referred to TXRX by key individuals on the Station Houston team and several client members of that organization. While I initially experienced difficulty in scheduling a visit and conversation, the wait and effect were well worth my while. 

On the day I was able to visit, even though the facility was receiving a large group of visitors from an area high school, I was personally met at the door by Mr. Ronnie Devries, TXRX Operations Manager, who proceeded to give me a detailed and extended tour of all the many and varied spaces and core areas, seeded across multiple buildings. Ronnie is affable, knowledgeable and welcoming, and his patter as we toured made this a most enjoyable experience. The facilities spaces, equipment an activities definitely speak to the dedicated "maker community" - both those who are on TXRX staff and the many, varied client members of the extensive organization. 

With obvious pride and excitement Mr. Devries shared that this bustling campus was experiencing such phenomenal growth the organization is now in the process of identifying a much larger capacity physical complex, in order to address the growth, expansion of services and diversity of programming. So inspired was I by the community, facilities and team of workers and volunteers of this not-for-profit organization, I was moved to begin introducing others to TXRX, and look forward to availing myself of their services, in future. 

A huge "thank you," to the TXRX family for being so welcoming and receptive to exploring the possibilities for collaboration, and to those who first commended this organization to me. Insofar as I am concerned (having only recently relocated to the Houston area), TXRX is exactly the kind of critical infrastructure needed in Houston...really, in any city of this size, in facilitating and inspiring its start-up and maker communities.

Respectfully submitted...

Jonas Moses (a fan)

text: Gosh I cannot say enough about Office Evolution except to say I am thrilled to have discovered it. As a business woman travelling the country I rely on temporary spaces such as these every once in awhile, and this one clearly sets the bar. Perfect location directly off the Sam Houston Parkway with plenty of great options for any type of space or budget you could possibly need. Clean and modern surroundings. The managing Director - Fritz Fowler could not have be more hospitable. This one's a keeper!

formatted_address: 1300 W Sam Houston Pkwy S Suite 100, Houston, TX 77042, USA
text: I have colleagues who office at Office Evolution and, on a recent trip to Houston, I needed a place to hang my hat.  Office Evolution was a great day office -- welcoming space; plenty of wonderful amenities; ample, free parking; and staff to help you get set up and make sure that you are working productively.  I will definitely come back when I need to park in Houston!

formatted_address: 1300 W Sam Houston Pkwy S Suite 100, Houston, TX 77042, USA
text: A very inviting place to conduct business and hold meetings. They offer refreshments, snacks, and keep a clean environment. Bree is the Receptionist; she is absolutely amazing! She is full of energy, helpful, and is also patient with everybody that walks through the door.

formatted_address: 1300 W Sam Houston Pkwy S Suite 100, Houston, TX 77042, USA
text: I worked with Fritz (Managing Partner) to tour the location. While I was working out some personal logistics, he let me try out the co-work space for a day. A professional atmosphere (but not uptight), plenty of open desks, plugs, fast wifi, and a nice kitchen set up. When comparing several locations in Houston, this one was the most affordable for the co-work option (so don't expect the bottomless soup and unlimited breadsticks option) but had everything that I needed. Fritz was willing to work with me, give him a call and he will do the same for you.

formatted_address: 1300 W Sam Houston Pkwy S Suite 100, Houston, TX 77042, USA

It's very clear the management cares about their clients and go above and beyond to make them happy.

text: Do Not! Do Not! I repeat do not lease here. This has been the most horrible and unimaginable experience I have ever had. I have lost business clients  from unwelcoming Staff, lost packages and important mail and items, clients unattended in the lobby without notifying me of their arrival, falsifying free parking to only charge you after you sign your contract, incorrect charges, and unauthorized charges from my bank account. Upon giving my notice I was promised a new office of a renovated area to only notify months later that all what was promised would be happening another year from now. DO NOT LEASE WITH THIS COMPANY. There was a car break-in that non of us tenants were notified about, which put all of our safety at risk especially women, along with months of not having working water, and a quarter exchange of staff that’s unsure about office protocol and procedures. Unacceptable, on every level. Save yourself a headache, I can barely perform professionally with all the stress. The worst is my clients have to experience this with me. Take my advice on this, run

text: The Co+Hoots space is seriously the best in Phoenix! Odeen, Jenny, and the whole team are so welcoming and kind and awesome! I love hanging out there :) So many good spaces to get work done in here, and such a cool vibe in the office. Everyone just wants to help everyone succeed. I definitely recommend this place to anyone interested in a collaborative work space that doesn't want to work from home.

formatted_address: 221 E Indianola Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85012, USA
text: Real cool spot! Very lively and good energy. Nice to be out of the house and get some good office time in. I’ll be back

formatted_address: 221 E Indianola Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85012, USA
text: This place is perfect for those looking to find a productive workspace! There are rooms to conduct meetings as well as private phone booths. There are regular events held onsite to aide in networking and growth. The staff is friendly, helpful, and knowledgeable. All of this at a great location!

formatted_address: 221 E Indianola Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85012, USA
text: This place is awesome! Came here with my work group and am considering signing up myself. Super awesome and clean environment. Feeling more efficient already!

formatted_address: 221 E Indianola Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85012, USA
text:
CO+Hoots is a clean, friendly and well-staffed co-working space. I host a meetup here once a month and am always happy with the condition of the facilitates, helpfulness of the staff, and friendliness of the other members.

Their "FlyBy" day passes are great for me as I only need the space once every month. When I need to take a quick call, their "phone booths" have a great audio quality by dampening any external sound. They have clean desks. The chairs are suitable for a days work.

With a great little coffee and kitchen area, if you need a break you can just step back there and relax a bit. If you need to get out, the location is in close proximity to many good restaurants.

The WiFi is solid and with covered parking (under the building), your vehicle doesn't have to bake in the sun all day on those hot Arizona days.

formatted_address: 1 N 1st St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text:
I utilize The Department for their conference room rentals to teach my courses when I am in Phoenix.  Their space is amazing and I always receive many great comments from all of my students.  They offer so many amenities that are rare and provide comfort to me and my team.

What really sets The Department apart is their staff.  Marissa and Hailey go out of their way to accommodate my group.  They are professional, kind, and welcoming.  My students often learn their names, because they are so impressed with their facilities and level of service.  Their communication throughout the rental process is fantastic.

I have returned here twice solely based on my experience with Marissa and Hailey.  I will continue to return as they make my job so easy  I can’t thank them enough!

formatted_address: 1 N 1st St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text:
📍The department is a little confusing to find but it’s right next to a coffee shop.. there is a glass door that remains locked at all times.

📍 The security guard must come out and let you enter. 

📍They offer a free trial of a Boot Camp which is a great way to test out and see if the program is a good fit.

formatted_address: 1 N 1st St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text:
I’ve worked at numerous co-working spaces in NYC, San Diego, Denver, and Phoenix, (WeWork, Spacious, Greendesk) and this is my favorite (and the best, in my opinion) by far. 
I’ve been working here off and on for over a year and love it. The staff, lead by Marissa, are incredibly professional, kind, helpful, and accommodating. It’s a great spot for working professionals and doesn’t have the busyness, loudness, or craziness of other chain co-working spaces. It’s creative and comfortable, and has all the resources you need for office work and more. It’s in a great location near plenty of coffee and food, and they even have Cartel coffee in house. They also have flexible desk/membership options and are more affordable than other spaces. If you want a creative, friendly, and professional space, this is your spot!

formatted_address: 1 N 1st St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text: Not only is this the best co-working space in the Phoenix valley, but if you're someone who needs to upload and download large files on a consistent basis, their internet set-up is the fastest I've encountered.  I am a filmmaker who works with remote editors and often times need to upload/download hundreds of gigabytes of footage, and never have an issue making it a productive workflow here.  The staff, the hospitality, and the members here make it a welcoming and creative environment to get work done and be around talented, hardworking individuals.

formatted_address: 1 N 1st St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text: I spent a few days at The Department renting out meeting room space during a conference. The staff was incredibly helpful and accommodating, and the space was lovely! We had access not only to the conference rooms we rented but also to the open space with comfortable chairs and desks and a well stocked kitchen. I would absolutely host meetings at The Department again.

formatted_address: 1415 N 7th Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85007, USA
text: This is an amazingly detailed and organized space with a fun and warm ambiance. All the tools you need for day to day office needs are on site and easily accessible. Such a professional and welcoming environment! Highly recommend The Office Bowl!

formatted_address: 1415 N 7th Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85007, USA
text:
A very nice workspace. Zero wifi issues. Easy access to food, office equipment, contemporary space that excites and inspires collaboration.  Really enjoying our time in this workspace. 

Logistics pluses free parking onsite, and easy to get to on 7th Ave at the West end of I-10 tunnel. 

And not least of all tasty Noms nearby... when we lift our heads from a marathon session to find a puppy to eat (jk), we can simply walk 500 feet to multiple tasty eateries (e.g. mad greens, ahi poke, breakfast shop, etc.. or cross the street to several more or simply recaffeinate at Starbucks. 

Overall #TheOfficeBowlWins!

text: Lovely, female-centric co-working place right in the Biltmore neighborhood.  My team has held our annual offsite working retreat at Hera Hub for two years in a row now, and everyone loves the warm atmosphere, large windows, and great amenities.

formatted_address: 2111 E Highland Ave #240, Phoenix, AZ 85016, USA
text: Hera Hub is a wondrous co-working space for women. Whether you are an entrepreneur or thinking of starting your own business or just need a place to hold meetings, interview or work on business plan or book, this is the place. It is spa-like and serene. Everyone is supportive and unintrusive. There are always courses and events going on. So many reasons to come through... and to even become a member!

text: Our team has been operating out of the Workuity space for just over a month and loving it here. Staff is fantastic and extremely prompt with any request. Location is great for recruiting and networking. Highly recommend Workuity if your looking for a place built to help businesses scale.

formatted_address: 2390 E Camelback Rd Suite 130, Phoenix, AZ 85016, USA
text: As a one person office of a national firm, Workuity provides the perfect environment. The lounge and building common areas are perfect for socializing.  You can't beat the location.

formatted_address: 515 E Grant St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text:
Galvanize is AWESOME. I've been here for nearly two years now and can honestly say no other social work hub comes close to value of Galvanize Phoenix. 

First of all, the energy is very high and infectious. You are surrounded by like-minded people, all of whom are working hard. I seem to get more done here than any of my other offices. 

The staff are extraordinarily nice and always looking to help you. They really go out of their way to make you get everything you need. 

The premises is pretty amazing. I purposely hold meetings here just to show off the glass, the steel and the space. My clients love it. 

Finally, the pricing is very reasonable. The lowest membership $250 a month is steal considering the access, the printing and conference room availability. 

It's for all these reasons that Galvanize has become the gold standard for social work hubs and spaces in Phoenix.

formatted_address: 515 E Grant St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text: Been at Galvanize for almost a year now. Can't say enough good things about the place. formatted_address: 515 E Grant St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text: Galvanize is an excellent coworking space! It overall has a great vibe and the community is extremely friendly. The location is also perfect, right near downtown phoenix. Thanks for being great, Galvanize!!

formatted_address: 515 E Grant St, Phoenix, AZ 85004, USA
text: With co-working spaces popping up all over the Valley, Galvanize outshines. Why? Community. Yes, the building is gorgeous. Yes, there's a top notch coding school and data science school. Here at Galvanize we build community.

formatted_address: 1020 E Missouri Ave, Phoenix, AZ 85014, USA
text:
I get multiples more work done when I office at the beautiful new Phoenix Better Business Bureau coworking space “ignite sparked by BBB” than I do nearby at my home office or my favorite resort. It’s set up for my success without the distractions at the other places. 

The staff, from President and CEO Matt Fehling to Director of Entrepreneur Programs Kimberly Roland, welcomed me along with their concierge team, gave me a tour, listened to what I’m up to, supported it and topped it off with delicious bottomless coffee from local nonprofit Cultivate.

I have a place to maximize everything admin for my 24 year matchmaking company SPIES. I set up dates and meet clients in private. If I met them here you’d all want to office here for sure!! 😄♥️

Today I worked on my laptop and used their excellent treadmill desk and knocked out 8200 steps. 

If you’re an Accredited BBB Business, there are offices in the Community Building next door you can reserve free! ignite sparked has two affordable offices open to everyone using the space. 

I love the bright yellow (DryBar yellow) touches and the motivational quotes everywhere. 

The final reason I’m working at the Phoenix BBB coworking space is to be surrounded by a powerful organization that leads with ethics! And fosters entrepreneurship. 

As a matchmaker, everything I do has to be with an ethical eye. I was in the Navy and am from the Midwest. SPIES was a Finalist in the Torch Awards for Ethics with the BBB. When I needed their wise consult this week, they were there for me and my company.

Kimberly Roland explained they plan to keep costs down because as a nonprofit, they are here to serve businesses. And consumers.

Thank you for a great first week! 
And great Wi-Fi.

formatted_address: 13835 N Northsight Blvd #100, Scottsdale, AZ 85260, USA
text: I love this place! It's a great place to buckle down and get to work on some exciting projects. The space is pretty large and open and allows a lot of natural light to come in. It's so inspiring, it had me coming in on the weekends to work! One person even said he'd sleep there if he could! I can understand that. The people there are also really nice, motivated, and supportive and...that's the true value in co-working: the people you didn't expect to meet!  Kristen works very hard to make sure everyone is satisfied. A lot of pretty, happy and healthy people over there.

formatted_address: 13835 N Northsight Blvd #100, Scottsdale, AZ 85260, USA

formatted_address: 4250 N Drinkwater Blvd Suite 300, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, USA
text: This is the 3rd workspace that I have been a part of in the phoenix area and Industrious is in a category by themselves. The vibe of the decor and office space is very cool with a great layout. They have created an killer community to be a part of and an experience I haven't found anywhere else in phoenix.

formatted_address: 4250 N Drinkwater Blvd Suite 300, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, USA
text: When I looked into space for my staff/team I found Industrious Scottsdale. formatted_address: 4435 E Chandler Blvd Suite 200, Phoenix, AZ 85048, USA
text:
If you need an office space... look no more. This is the best option out there and I'll give a few of the reasons: 1. Location is great, close to freeway, nice part of town, restaurants close by. 2. Facilities are brand new and very clean. 3. Pricing options are great depending on your needs. 4. Fresh ground coffee available to all tenants and very nice break room with microwave, refrigerator, and REAL forks, spoons, plates, glasses... that might sound unimportant, but it's better for the environment because we don't have to rely on the disposable plastic ones. 5. Management team is very friendly, they make you feel welcome and part of the community. In addition to that, the variety of people that you interact with is quite interesting. 
In conclusion, I love it here!

formatted_address: 7014 E Camelback Rd Suite B100A, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, USA
text: Since starting my own design firm a couple years ago, I have been part of two co-working spaces and toured many others to find the environment that fits with our brand. When starting off on your own, you want to feel confident when bringing a client to your office. Industrious at Fashion Square lets you do that without all of the baggage of finding an office where all of the day to day is up to you as far as IT, common areas, and a respectable location. This location provides you with instant credibility and the ability to focus on your business without all of the extracurricular headache that normally goes on.

formatted_address: 7014 E Camelback Rd Suite B100A, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, USA
text:
Susies review is factual but I wonder if she spent any time working at this Industrious location.

The review is based upon what was promised by the sales person and industrious marketing material.

Our team has been working here since day one.

Pros; beautiful decor, large common areas, good location.

Con; lack of food, snacks, drinks throughout the day and evening. Lack of attentiveness and response from the community manager (Doug) with existing members/tenants. Lack of signage in the mall, difficult for guest to enter. Retention, several members are already leaving.

Areas to focus on; customer service to existing members/tenants. Members/tenants are paying a premium price and they expect what was marketed, sold, promised to them. 

Once again, this is a factual review based upon first hand experience. I hope these issues are addressed, I would love to see this location be a success if not we are leaving next month.

formatted_address: 7014 E Camelback Rd Suite B100A, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, USA
text:
I have toured many different co-working spaces throughout greater Phoenix and the Industrious location at Fashion Square is at or near the top. 

From the prime and unique location at Fashion Square to the beautifully designed interior there are some elements that are simply unmatched. The communal space and shared conference rooms are Class A and rival any Scottsdale or Phoenix office. I was especially impressed by the ability to customize space meet the needs of the individual members and companies.

Overall, the space is very impressive and I’m confident many companies/members will love working here.

formatted_address: 7014 E Camelback Rd Suite B100A, Scottsdale, AZ 85251, USA
text:
From impeccable decor to day-to-day hospitality, this location has proven themselves to be the best in the Scottsdale area. Our company moved in from a competing co-working space and simply assumed our needs were too unreasonable for a shared environment. We were pleasantly surprised upon arrival and contrary to our anticipations, service did not decline but rather improved substantially as the staff got to know ours.

This location is large, but they do a great job at tending to each and every one of their tenants. Doug and his team are prompt, professional and personable. They take pride in assisting your team and giving your visiting clients a first-class experience. 

Thorough orientations, fast internet, ample shared spaces, and refreshments to keep you feeling revitalized - highly, highly recommend!! They without a doubt carry through on their brand promise of making you “love where you work”.

formatted_address: 2001 Market St #2500, Philadelphia, PA 19103, USA
text:
I maintained a membership at the 17/Market MakeOffices for about 2 months last year. Though the facility was clean and new, the space for members who did not purchase offices was one long rectangular table, in the middle of the windowless common room area. It soon wore on me and I decided to switch to Indy Hall, which has been a much better experience. 

That in-and-of-itself would not constitute a 1-star review, but it has been almost 4 months since I decided to cancel my membership, and I am still waiting for them to return my security deposit. I have emailed multiple times, but the check has yet to arrive. I would not recommend MakeOffices.

text: Great place, super trendy, clean, great facility! Great for startups and existing businesses. They also have networking events to grow and help other businesses. -Julia

business_name: The Yard - Coworking Office Space Philadelphia
formatted_address: 21 S 11th St, Philadelphia, PA 19107, USA
text:
I had a job interview there. I can understand why up-and-coming entrepreneurs would be attracted to such a space: it's fresh-looking professional space for those who can't quite afford their own brick-and-mortar space to conduct business but don't want to meet clients at their home offices or at, say, a coffeehouse. 

The 3rd floor rooms are soundproof but all share an clean open reception area, a conference room, and a kitchenette. Everyone can feel like they're doing corner-office work and can bring their clients and interviewees to a place that represents them and their companies well.

If I had the money to rent there, I would!

business_name: The Yard - Coworking Office Space Philadelphia
formatted_address: 21 S 11th St, Philadelphia, PA 19107, USA
text: When I first started my membership I loved the yard Emily was great. She treated my guest with respect and they felt welcome. After Emily left things went downhill. The new receptionist were rude and inconsiderate. The students that I mentored complained about them and their parents. I left as soon as my contract was up.

business_name: The Yard - Coworking Office Space Philadelphia
formatted_address: 21 S 11th St, Philadelphia, PA 19107, USA
text: Nice working environment. The offices are simple but comfortable and the shared open spaces have some basic amenities like coffee and tea. I do like the digital locks and the WiFi is generally pretty reliable even for our group.

business_name: The Yard - Coworking Office Space Philadelphia
formatted_address: 21 S 11th St, Philadelphia, PA 19107, USA
text:
Forget the milkshake, I want The Yard! 

I came here on a whim for a art exhibition and was pleasantly surprised by the The Yard's offerings. 

The Yard is a co-working space offering a place for anyone to rent space to not only work but network as well. The building is right near Chinatown/Jefferson area - so lots of foot traffic and slim parking! 

The night I visited was when they were having an art gallery of works by different artists (both local and national) being showcased throughout the space on all the floors. It's a nice touch to exhibit the art in a more real environment - gave the pieces a home.

Outside of the workspace provided, The Yard has amenities such as coffee, drinks, WiFi to list a few. The space really enhances collaboration, and brings creativity to the forefront.

For anyone that needs an area to get work done, network, get their creative juices flowing, etc. this place has all the offerings!

formatted_address: 4323 Main St, Philadelphia, PA 19127, USA
text:
Lia Meneker hosted the first of what will be weekly Thursday night open mic sessions in this co-working space on Valentine's day night in 2019. Jillian, the events coordinator said she hoped this space could become s place where people come to collaborate and to make friends and I think that started happening.

There were many guitarists together with a smattering of other musicians, including a couple of keyboardists, a rapper and a flugelhorn player. Most of the work was original, and there were a few improvisational collaborations, including a jam after the open mic was over. 

People responded warmly to most of the musician's efforts. That kind of kindness is really helpful in developing the confidence and camradery that can keep people coming back just to see a wide variety of material, presented at a variety of levels of expertise. 

The fact that that camradery seemed to be developing bodes well for the future of this event. I think all the musician's really appreciated Lia's efforts. I hope people continue to check out this event and expect it to be a fun evening in the future.

text:
An awesome, local non-profit offering the local community access to a multitude of tools, equipment and space available to create their ideas and fulfill long desired projects.  

This organization allows one to pursue anything from a DIY project, yet don't have the equipment and space to complete, to attending a class to learn a new skill such as welding, laser cutting or how to use & create w/a 3D printer. And so much more!

8000 I-10 Frontage Rd, San Antonio, TX 78230, USA
text:
I was a tenant for 2 and a half years and it was the worst experience of my life!!
 Almost made me wana close my business being harassed by them every day and every week.  If you are a start up company this is not the place for you!!!! You will get nickle and dime to death!!! Copies, packages, phone patching, forwarding calls, etc., Signed a lease for $700 and my bill was usually $1,000-$1,100 Lost tons of potential business with their phone systems too, but if you have someone in that office and calls not forwarded to your cell you will be okay.
   If you have a established business and looking for a 
Professional place to move with a receptionist to answer your phones how you need them to be answered like a accounting company, lawer or high profile business then this is the place for you! Great atmosphere, stunning view of the city from their 15th floor office and great prices for renting a conferance room for professional business meetings. 
 Their contacts autorenew unless you give them written notice 2 months in advance, but certainly careful because they will still autorenew your contract! Gave them my notice for a 6 month contract so I can move out and they would not give it to me?! They said I never notified them and was in another 1 year contract. Luckily I save all my emails and they acknowledged it with a approved movers list so I was able to get my 6 month lease instead of a year lease. Was a long waste of time going back and forth. They also would forget to apply payments to my account sometimes but luckily I kept all my reciepts. Printer is always breaking too, very frustrating when you have a client and have to have him sign papers but cant print them out (happened multiple times). But If you have extra money to pay the fee to have a printer in your office you'll be fine. And never ask for a discount on your bill, I asked for a $50 discount for copies I didnt make they added $250 onto my final bill and gave me a $50 discount I asked for lol. Never had a complete month where I recieved all my amenities I paid for and got tired of having to email them about it and finally gave up.
Happy I'm finally out of there!! 😁
  
(This is corporate america at its finest!)

text:
Honestly go rent somewhere else. 

Made a appointment to take one last look to insure it's the right fit for me and my business and to find out the prices. I was debating on two suite/ room numbers. So when I finally made my decision and wanted to put down the first months rent I notified one of the realtors who showed me the place (Charles) .Not once was there mentioned what type of business they want in there as long as your business didn't have that strong nail spa scent which mine doesn't your all good. (spray tanning doesn't have a oder to it). The same day I notified Charles a few hours later I get this voicemail from the owner Jerry Hagee so I called him back that's when he said that my type of business doesn't fall under his vision for the office box so I wont be able to rent from him, yet no where on their website does is say what type of business he envisioned for the office box, this is what the website says:"OFFICE BOX® is a good fit for freelancers, entrepreneurs, home based and mobile workers. The goal is to build a unique diverse community of professionals in our shared office space where collaboration, networking and creativity flows". 

In the voicemail he left he says "for something like that(my type of business) I'll have to sign a 3 year lease otherwise I won't be able to lease it" like what ??? you advertised it as a no commitment month to month deal yet you want me to sign a 3yr contract! So not cool, just because you can't get the rooms rented out doesn't mean you start putting people on contracts.

I wasn't going to leave a review I was planning on just to let it go but at the end of the day what stops them from doing it the next person that gets excited about the space only to get crushed down

text:
I live in Pacific Beach and looked FOREVER trying to find a coworking space nearby. The only ones were in Downtown, La Jolla, Little Italy, North Park, or North County. But I didn't want to waste time commuting far away. As a result, I ended getting a shared office space in La Jolla, but it was a still pain getting there every day. 

Finally, I heard someone opened a coworking space in Pacific Beach, so I checked it out, and immediately signed a lease with Ray. 

The office is clean, a great location, and everyone at the space is nice. If you're looking to work a few blocks away from the beach ... look no further. I can't suggest Ray's space enough.

formatted_address: 1111 Sixth Ave, San Diego, CA 92101, USA
text: After being constantly distracted while attempting to work from home, I finally decided to give co-working a try. I’ve been coming to Novel for a couple months now, and my productivity has increased dramatically. I picked this place over other coworking spaces nearby because it was less expensive, but worried that it might be worse quality. Luckily, I have had no issues at all. text:

formatted_address: 4610 Park Blvd, San Diego, CA 92116, USA
text:
The place is unprofessional. Period. The person in charge was cold and short. When I asked a question  -- his answer twice was, "Did you see our website?" in an offended tone.

He did not answer my questions. Rude. And yes, I did see the website -- and it wasn't coherent...

So this guy brought me to the very back room and plopped us in front of a garbage can, and said, "Here, let's talk here at the trash can."  Literally. 

(*cricket* you have large space, why here, sir?) 

When I asked if I could bring my clients into common areas, he replied, "you can meet here at the trash can," trying to be funny, but he still acted annoyed with my question. (Gee, thanks, but really, why do you keep bringing up the trash can in your enormous building?) 

He then downplayed his venue and space to ME -- and I'm sure he has his reasons... which I'd rather not know. 

I actually felt he was going out of his way to make me feel uncomfortable. He even began pitching me about co-working spaces downtown, at which point, he finally smiled and was actually trying to persuade me. 

Was my lisp too loud for his establishment? Or were my pants too pink? I can't think of any other reason I'd be treated so poorly. Meanwhile, I sent another lispy friend of mine to check the space out and he had the same horrible customer service experience.
